xt":"But the key here is the anxiety about having a serious illness rather than the symptoms being amplified.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04323,0.07732,0.08136,0.085031,0.088661,0.091143,0.09367,0.094421,0.090893,0.090933,0.084196,0.079142],"unified_progress":[0.052283,0.065767,0.07336,0.080569,0.086301,0.091297,0.093158,0.09684,0.095427,0.097597,0.089566,0.077837]},{"section":15,"text":"Since the patient is fixated on the fear of having a specific disease and keeps seeking reassurance, illness anxiety disorder fits better.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051778,0.085011,0.082431,0.082278,0.084311,0.087374,0.087838,0.089697,0.086523,0.087329,0.083408,0.092023],"unified_progress":[0.060992,0.066605,0.070397,0.075397,0.079077,0.085113,0.086314,0.091293,0.091378,0.093309,0.097392,0.10274]},{"section":16,"text":"Another thought: could it be a delusional disorder?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033747,0.064867,0.077907,0.085817,0.093001,0.093715,0.09713,0.099269,0.09723,0.097211,0.088006,0.072102],"unified_progress":[0.041237,0.066354,0.081983,0.093734,0.094553,0.09473,0.098615,0.097959,0.095296,0.09391,0.080233,0.061396]},{"section":17,"text":"But delusions are fixed false beliefs that don't change even with contrary evidence.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039703,0.071935,0.077503,0.083607,0.090295,0.094268,0.097522,0.098286,0.094343,0.092591,0.084797,0.075151],"unified_progress":[0.050613,0.067025,0.077785,0.08591,0.091561,0.09505,0.096725,0.09834,0.094828,0.094277,0.081965,0.065921]},{"section":18,"text":"However, the case doesn't mention that the belief is fixed to the point of being delusional, just that he's not convinced.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050273,0.084277,0.081812,0.082151,0.085702,0.090541,0.092082,0.095204,0.0908,0.08924,0.082758,0.075162],"unified_progress":[0.062616,0